Sachet water sellers in Kano are making brisk business due to the current hot weather in the state, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. Some of the vendors, who spoke with NAN on Wednesday in Kano, said they have been making huge sales in the past one week. They said that the current hot weather condition in the city and the turnover has also induced many youths to go into the business. Ada Uche, one of the vendors at France Road, said she sells a truckload of sachet water on a daily basis with a profit of N2000. Also, Hajiya Yasira Hamis, said that the business has afforded her the opportunity to assist her husband financially. (NAN)  